  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Introduction RYGB surgeon; Have become increasingly morbid obesity treatment methods with
      improvements in minimally invasive surgery. Ensuring patient comfort and early return to life
      are the criteria that should be given priority in this treatment method. The purpose of this
      study is to determine the use of drain, which closely affects these criteria; And the effect
      on patient comfort.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      Question the necessity of routine use of drain in RYGB surgeon
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
